data.content:
Yes — use `Assert.IsInstanceOfType<T>()`. In MSTest v3+ it returns the typed instance, so you can assert on properties without casting:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void Create_ReturnsCorrectHandler()
{
    var factory = new HandlerFactory();
    var result = factory.Create("email");

    var handler = Assert.IsInstanceOfType<EmailHandler>(result);
    Assert.AreEqual("email", handler.Type);
}
```

This gives you a clearer failure message (expected type vs actual type) and removes the risk of an undiagnostic `InvalidCastException`.
